definition: to be born/to give birth/life/to grow/raw/uncooked/student
earth/dust/clay/local/indigenous/crude opium/unsophisticated/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]

sentences.english: But as a local born and bred Liverpudlian person.
sentences.chinese: 但作爲一名土生土長的利物浦人。

sentences.english: I was born and raised in Kaohsiung.
sentences.chinese: 我是土生土長的高雄人。

sentences.english: The elections were over and the first native Governor was inaugurated.
sentences.chinese: 選舉結束，第一個在當地土生土長的州長走馬上任了。

sentences.english: The soil here is very moist.
sentences.chinese: 我是土生土長的深圳人。

sentences.english: I, you know, I was born and raised in the Bay, so.
sentences.chinese: 我是土生土長的舊金山灣區人。

sentences.english: Rock flayers are one of Outland's indigenous species.
sentences.chinese: 岩石劫掠者是外域一種土生土長的物種。

sentences.english: Another home-grown proverb is Every dog is allowed one bite.
sentences.chinese: 另一句土生土長的格言是，“每條狗允許咬一次人”。

sentences.english: To tell you the truth , I was born and raised in kaohsiung.
sentences.chinese: 老實說，我是土生土長的高雄人。

sentences.english: My name is Karim Davis, and I am a native-born American from the city of Memphis, Tennessee.
sentences.chinese: 是一個土生土長的田納西州孟斐斯市的美國人。

sentences.english: The local houses are all fishermen's homes.
sentences.chinese: 土生土長的房，全是捕魚人營造的家。

sentences.english: Europe, at least the indigenous population of Europe, is dying.
sentences.chinese: 歐洲，至少是土生土長的歐洲人，正在消亡。

sentences.english: All Londoners who are born within the sound of Bow Bells are called cockneys.
sentences.chinese: 所有土生土長的倫敦人被稱爲是倫敦佬。

sentences.english: A native of Germany, Govi spent eight years living in India.
sentences.chinese: 他是土生土長的德國人，但在印度生活了八年之久。

sentences.english: Another one was I live, I've grown up in LA.
sentences.chinese: 另一個原因是我因爲我土生土長在洛杉磯。

sentences.english: A tulou building usually consists of packed earth on the outer wall and a wooden internal framework.
sentences.chinese: 土樓通常由生土夯築而成，內部爲木製結構。
